## [ Visual Studio ]
.vs/
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.doccache

## [ Build outputs ]
bin/
obj/
[Ee]xternals/
TestResults/

## [ Node/Frontend (if applicable) ]
node_modules/
dist/
npm-debug.log*

## [ Environment & Secrets ]
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
appsettings.Development.json
# Note: Some teams commit Development.json, but never commit 
# appsettings.Production.json or secrets.json.
secrets.json
*.ntvs_analysis.dat

## [ Entity Framework & Databases ]
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
Migrations/
# Only ignore Migrations if you prefer to manage them manually; 
# usually, it's better to keep them tracked.

## [ Operating System Files ]
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

## [ Packages ]
*.nupkg
# NuGet packages are usually restored on build, not stored in Git
**/packages/*
!**/packages/build/